data.description: Single story living with a fully renovated master bathroom on a spacious, level lot in a subdivision with no HOA! Sound too good to be true!? Welcome to 20 Paces Lakes Drive! As you first enter the home you’ll notice the neutral walls and flooring are ready to match any décor. The stone fireplace in the family room not only acts as a focal point to the room but on these chilly fall evenings it’s perfect to add some additional warmth and coziness to the space.     The split bedroom plan is a perfect arrangement so that the owner’s suite is situated quietly away from guests or other family members. This arrangement also works nicely should the extra bedrooms be utilized as a home office or play space for little ones.     The eat-in kitchen features clean lines while the rich toned cabinets and stainless appliances give an elevated look to the functional space. When entertaining the dining space is versatile enough to accommodate a sit-down family dinner or can be used as a spot to serve appetizers, finger foods, party food or game day snacks, regardless of the occasion.     If you want your owner’s suite to be that quiet, private area to get away from stresses of the day and just kickback and relax as this bedroom and fully updated and customized bath will deliver. To start with you’ll enter the space through an exquisite set of barn doors which not only add a stylish, farmhouse flair to the space but also are functional in providing a wide enough opening to accommodate a wheelchair or to move large furniture in or out of the space.  The bedroom offers plenty of wall space to allow for furniture arrangement, while the hardwood floors provide a warm, clean feel to the space. The owner’s bath is accessed behind another barn door which provides extra wide access to the bath, which has been completely upgraded and customized, including a roll-in shower with frameless surround. The tile floor in the bath and shower, as well as the subway tile shower walls and granite vanity top all feature relaxing earth tones. In addition there is a step-in tub and grab bars in the shower to offer ease of access and extra assistance. There’s plenty of space in the generous closet, which is tucked away behind a pocket door, in addition to additional storage for linens and personal belongings that can be tucked away in the soft close vanity drawers or in the ample shelving that’s behind stylish shaker cabinet doors.    We are coming into a great time to enjoy the outdoors so grab a glass of sweet tea, your favorite book and a sweater and sit out on the screen porch and enjoy the crisp fall air. There's so much space in the private, fenced backyard, creating a blank canvas for how to use the space, but think about a football game with family and friends after Thanksgiving dinner, a place for a play or swings, sandbox cornhole, badminton, horseshoes or just a place for youngsters or four-legged friends to run off some energy.    All of this and some additional peace of mind that comes along with knowing the water heater was replaced in 2020 and the AC compressor was replaced in 2022.     Enjoy the rural location of Paces Lakes while still having convenient access to a grocery store, fast food restaurants, schools and White Oak Park, all of which is just minutes away. For additional shopping, dining and entertainment Downtown Dallas and The Silver Comet Trail are just a short ten-minute drive.
